author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. 10-Year Bond Yield Falls to Near 2% on Lackluster U.S. Data
text:
U.S. government bonds strengthened Wednesday, pushing the yield on the 10-year Treasury note down to near 2%, as fresh signs of tepid consumer spending and low inflation boosted demand for haven assets.
